    "86) with the parameters 'n_neighbors = 30, n_components = 2, min_dist = 0.15, metric = 'jaccard', random_state = 1'.",
    "The heat maps in Fig. 3 were generated using the heatmap.2 package in R, with agglomerative clustering using median linkage on Euclidean distances.",
    "Third, to study the specific plasmids from PS974 and PS1110 in Fig. 5f and Supplementary Fig.",
    "14 (contig names in Supplementary Table 11), we ran Bowtie 2 on each sequence separately.",
    "This set-up allowed every read to potentially align to multiple sequences, resulting in a more complete estimation of which metagenomes contained a plasmid."
